<subSubSection lastPageId="105" lastPageNumber="106" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="105" lastPageNumber="106" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
The name first appeared in 1822 on the captions for plate 1 of the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Mélanopsides">&quot;Melanopsides</normalizedToken>
fossiles&quot; in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Férussac’s">Ferussac's</normalizedToken>
&quot;Histoire naturelle&quot; (see also introduction for details). While 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferussac, AEJPJFd'Audebard de" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris" pageId="308" pageNumber="309" pagination="132 - 164" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/23445page/148/mode/1up" refId="B144" refString="Ferussac, AEJPJFd'Audebard de, 1823. Monographie des especes vivantes et fossiles du genre melanopside, Melanopsis, et observations geologiques a leur sujet. Memoires de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris 1 (1): 132 - 164, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/23445page/148/mode/1up" title="Monographie des especes vivantes et fossiles du genre melanopside, Melanopsis, et observations geologiques a leur sujet." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/23445page/148/mode/1up" volume="1" year="1823">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Férussac">Ferussac</normalizedToken>
(1823)
</bibRefCitation>
included also recent specimens under that name in his monograph on the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H.Adams &amp; A.Adams" authorityYear="1854" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Not" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Melanopsidae</taxonomicName>
, the only specimen illustrated in 1822 in the &quot;Histoire naturelle&quot; was a fossil one from the Miocene of France. This fact remained widely unknown to biologists and paleontologists alike. Only few malacologists, such as 
<bibRefCitation author="Grateloup, J-PS de" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin d'Histoire Naturelle de la Societe linneenne de Bordeaux" pageId="312" pageNumber="313" pagination="72 - 109" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/110491page/82/mode/1up" refId="B201" refString="Grateloup, J-PS de, 1828. Tableau des coquilles Fossiles qu'on rencontre dans des terrains calcaires tertiaires (faluns) des environs de Dax, dans le departement des Landes (Articles 1-3). Bulletin d'Histoire Naturelle de la Societe linneenne de Bordeaux 2: 72 - 109, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/110491page/82/mode/1up" title="Tableau des coquilles Fossiles qu'on rencontre dans des terrains calcaires tertiaires (faluns) des environs de Dax, dans le departement des Landes (Articles 1 - 3)." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/110491page/82/mode/1up" volume="2" year="1828">Grateloup (1828</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Grateloup, J-PS de" journalOrPublisher="Actes de la Societe linneenne de Bordeaux" pageId="312" pageNumber="313" pagination="92 - 152" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/101658page/30/mode/1up" refId="B202" refString="Grateloup, J-PS de, 1838. Conchyliologie fossile du bassin de l'Adour. (3.me Memoire). V. Memoire sur les Coquilles fossiles des Mollusques terrestres et fluviatiles (de la classe des Tracheliopodes) observees dans les terrains tertiaires du bassin de l'Adour. Actes de la Societe linneenne de Bordeaux 10: 92 - 152, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/101658page/30/mode/1up" title="Conchyliologie fossile du bassin de l'Adour. (3. me Memoire). V. Memoire sur les Coquilles fossiles des Mollusques terrestres et fluviatiles (de la classe des Tracheliopodes) observees dans les terrains tertiaires du bassin de l'Adour." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/101658page/30/mode/1up" volume="10" year="1838">1838</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Grateloup, J-PS de" journalOrPublisher="Th. Lafargue, Bordeaux" pageId="312" pageNumber="313" publicationUrl="https://books.google.at/books?id=A-oQAAAAIAAJ&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;hl=de&amp;source=gbs_ge_summary_r&amp;cad=0v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false" refId="B203" refString="Grateloup, J-PS de, 1840. Conchyliologie fossile des terrains tertiaires du bassin de l'Adour (environs de Dax). Tome 1: Univalves. Atlas. Th. Lafargue, Bordeaux, https://books.google.at/books?id=A-oQAAAAIAAJ&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;hl=de&amp;source=gbs_ge_summary_r&amp;cad=0v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false" title="Conchyliologie fossile des terrains tertiaires du bassin de l'Adour (environs de Dax). Tome 1: Univalves. Atlas" url="https://books.google.at/books?id=A-oQAAAAIAAJ&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;hl=de&amp;source=gbs_ge_summary_r&amp;cad=0v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false" year="1840">1840</bibRefCitation>
), used the name correctly and attributed it to the French fossils. Consequently, none of the specimens referred to as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferussac" authorityYear="1822" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melanopsis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanopsis dufourii" order="Pteropoda" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="dufourii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Melanopsis dufourii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the biological literature actually corresponds to the real 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferussac" authorityYear="1822" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melanopsis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanopsis dufourii" order="Pteropoda" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="dufourii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Melanopsis dufourii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Very likely, some of 
<pageBreakToken pageId="105" pageNumber="106" start="start">the</pageBreakToken>
other melanopsids from Dax (see, e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Grateloup, J-PS de" journalOrPublisher="Actes de la Societe linneenne de Bordeaux" pageId="312" pageNumber="313" pagination="92 - 152" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/101658page/30/mode/1up" refId="B202" refString="Grateloup, J-PS de, 1838. Conchyliologie fossile du bassin de l'Adour. (3.me Memoire). V. Memoire sur les Coquilles fossiles des Mollusques terrestres et fluviatiles (de la classe des Tracheliopodes) observees dans les terrains tertiaires du bassin de l'Adour. Actes de la Societe linneenne de Bordeaux 10: 92 - 152, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/101658page/30/mode/1up" title="Conchyliologie fossile du bassin de l'Adour. (3. me Memoire). V. Memoire sur les Coquilles fossiles des Mollusques terrestres et fluviatiles (de la classe des Tracheliopodes) observees dans les terrains tertiaires du bassin de l'Adour." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/101658page/30/mode/1up" volume="10" year="1838">Grateloup 1838</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="D'Orbigny, A" journalOrPublisher="Victor Masson, Paris" pageId="307" pageNumber="308" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/98989page/9/mode/1up" refId="B130" refString="D'Orbigny, A, 1852. Prodrome de Paleontologie. Stratigraphique universelle des animaux mollusques et rayonnes faisant suitre au cours elementaire de paleontologie et de geologie stratigraphique. Troisieme volume. Victor Masson, Paris, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/98989page/9/mode/1up" title="Prodrome de Paleontologie. Stratigraphique universelle des animaux mollusques et rayonnes faisant suitre au cours elementaire de paleontologie et de geologie stratigraphique. Troisieme volume." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/98989page/9/mode/1up" year="1852">
<normalizedToken originalValue="d’Orbigny">d'Orbigny</normalizedToken>
1852
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pallary, P" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de l'Afrique du Nord" pageId="323" pageNumber="324" pagination="70 - 87" publicationUrl="http://bibdigital.rjb.csic.es/spa/Libro.php?Libro=1840" refId="B378" refString="Pallary, P, 1916. Observations relatives a la nomenclature des Melanopsis fossiles. Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de l'Afrique du Nord 7 (3): 70 - 87, http://bibdigital.rjb.csic.es/spa/Libro.php?Libro=1840" title="Observations relatives a la nomenclature des Melanopsis fossiles." url="http://bibdigital.rjb.csic.es/spa/Libro.php?Libro=1840" volume="7" year="1916">Pallary 1916</bibRefCitation>
) are unrecognized junior synonyms of this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
The names &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melanopsis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="dufouri" order="Pteropoda" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="dufouri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">dufouri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; as mentioned by numerous authors and databases and &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melanopsis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="dufourei" order="Pteropoda" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="dufourei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">dufourei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; as given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Morelet, A" journalOrPublisher="Journal de Conchyliologie" pageId="320" pageNumber="321" pagination="280 - 305" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/53861page/286/mode/1up" refId="B321" refString="Morelet, A, 1853. Catalogue des Mollusques terrestres et fluviatiles de l'Algerie. Journal de Conchyliologie 4: 280 - 305, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/53861page/286/mode/1up" title="Catalogue des Mollusques terrestres et fluviatiles de l'Algerie." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/53861page/286/mode/1up" volume="4" year="1853">Morelet (1853</bibRefCitation>
: 297) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Bourguignat, JR" journalOrPublisher="Annales de Malacologie" pageId="303" pageNumber="304" pagination="1 - 168" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/55067page/9/mode/1up" refId="B48" refString="Bourguignat, JR, 1884. Histoire des melaniens du systeme europeen. Annales de Malacologie 2: 1 - 168, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/55067page/9/mode/1up" title="Histoire des melaniens du systeme europeen." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/55067page/9/mode/1up" volume="2" year="1884">Bourguignat (1884</bibRefCitation>
: 114) are incorrect subsequent spellings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
